&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THEATRES, ANAESTHETICS, CRITICAL CARE AND PAIN DIRECTORATE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;OPERATING THEATRES&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;JOB TITLE: TEAM LEADER – PLASTICS AND RECONSTRUCTIVE SURGERY&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PAY BAND: 6&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;HOURS: 37½ HOURS PER WEEK&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PERMANENT CONTRACT&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen within our Operating Theatres for a full-time Team Leader for our Plastics and Reconstructive Surgery Theatre.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidates must be registered with the Nursing Midwifery Council or the Health Care Professions Council and have substantial theatre experience at Band 5 level. Experience in plastics and reconstructive surgery, and an in-depth knowledge and understanding of surgical techniques and associated equipment is also essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is essential that the successful candidates have evidence of providing support and training to students and other staff, and regular study since qualification.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hywel Rees on 01384 456111 Ext: 2602&lt;/p&gt;
